# Documentation Standards

_Rules for code documentation, project documentation, and comment quality_

## Code Documentation

**ID**: code-documentation  
**Severity**: warning  

Standards for documenting code

- Document all public functions and classes
- Use JSDoc for JavaScript/TypeScript
- Use docstrings for Python
- Update documentation when changing code

## Project Documentation

**ID**: project-documentation  
**Severity**: warning  

Standards for project-level documentation

- Maintain up-to-date README files for all major components
- Document architectural decisions in ADRs
- Keep API documentation synchronized with implementation
- Use diagrams for visualizing complex systems

## Comment Quality

**ID**: comment-quality  
**Severity**: info  

Standards for code comments

- Focus comments on why, not what
- Update comments when changing the related code
- Remove redundant comments
- Use TODO comments with issue references for future work

